From 12e383b659fd8a1cbd63d1671b5eb1e676a0d1bb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Benjamin Tissoires <bentiss@kernel.org>
Date: Mon, 4 May 2026 10:47:22 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 6/7] HID: pass the buffer size to hid_report_raw_event

commit 0a3fe972a7cb ("HID: core: Mitigate potential OOB by removing
bogus memset()") enforced the provided data to be at least the size of
the declared buffer in the report descriptor to prevent a buffer
overflow. However, we can try to be smarter by providing both the buffer
size and the data size, meaning that hid_report_raw_event() can make
better decision whether we should plaining reject the buffer (buffer
overflow attempt) or if we can safely memset it to 0 and pass it to the
rest of the stack.

Fixes: 0a3fe972a7cb ("HID: core: Mitigate potential OOB by removing bogus memset()")
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Benjamin Tissoires <bentiss@kernel.org>
Cherry-picked-for: https://gitlab.archlinux.org/archlinux/packaging/packages/linux/-/work_items/195
